      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "content": "Workflow Overview\nThis is a QuickBooks webhook router that receives notifications from QuickBooks Online and routes different transaction types to specialized sub-workflows.\nStep-by-Step Breakdown\n1. Webhook Trigger\n\nReceives POST requests from QuickBooks at endpoint /841c1c3c-9326-4adf-9565-11c93a7ca72e\nQuickBooks sends notifications when invoices, estimates, purchase orders, or payments are created/updated\n\n2. Extract from File\n\nExtracts the raw text from the webhook payload\n\n3. JsonParse (Code Node)\n\nParses the nested JSON structure from QuickBooks\nExtracts key event properties: specversion, id, source, type, time, intuitentityid, intuitaccountid\nThe type field indicates what kind of transaction it is (invoice, estimate, payment, etc.)\n\n4. If Node - Invoice Check\n\nTRUE path: If type contains \"invoice\" → proceeds to fetch additional invoice details\nFALSE path: All other transaction types → skip directly to Switch\n\n5. HTTP Request4 (TRUE path only)\n\nFetches the full invoice details from QuickBooks API\nURL: https://quickbooks.api.intuit.com/v3/company/9341454112300561/invoice/{intuitentityid}?include=enhancedAllCustomFields\nThis retrieves custom fields to determine if it's a regular invoice or pro-forma\n\n6. Code in JavaScript\n\nExamines the CustomField[0].StringValue from the invoice\nIf value = '2': Sets invoiceType = \"Pro-Forma\"\nIf value = '1' or empty: Sets invoiceType = \"Invoice\"\n\n7. Merge\n\nCombines the original webhook data with the invoice type classification\n\n8. Aggregate\n\nConsolidates all the data into a single item for the Switch node\n\n9. Switch Node - Transaction Router\nRoutes to different sub-workflows based on transaction type:\n\nOutput 0: invoiceType contains \"Invoice\" → Call 'QB Invoice' workflow\nOutput 1: type contains \"estimate\" → Call 'QB Estimate' workflow\nOutput 2: type contains \"purchaseorder\" → Call 'QB (Purchase Order)' workflow\nOutput 3: type contains \"payment\" → Call 'QB SR' (Sales Receipt/Payment) workflow\nOutput 4: invoiceType equals \"Pro-Forma\" → Call 'QB (PRO-FORMA)' workflow\n\nKey Logic\nThe workflow handles a special case for invoices: it distinguishes between regular invoices and pro-forma invoices using a custom field. All other transaction types are routed based solely on their type property from the webhook.\nThis is essentially a smart dispatcher that ensures each QuickBooks transaction type gets processed by its appropriate specialized workflow.",
          "height": 1120,
          "width": 864
        },
